## Finding (resolved by T.QA.6 patch)

**Prior linter limitation:** The linter did not skip content inside markdown fenced code blocks
(` ``` ` delimiters). This ADR contains a `## QA Plan` heading at line 120 inside a fenced code block
(the D2 section's format-example). That embedded heading was detected as the first `## QA Plan`
occurrence; the body of that code-block section contains `**UI involvement:** yes | no` (the template
placeholder), which failed the `yes|no` validation check.

**Fix landed in T.QA.6:** `has_qa_plan_heading` and `get_qa_plan_body` in
`scripts/hooks/pre-commit-zz-plan-structure.sh` now track a `fence` flag that toggles on each
` ``` ` line, and skip heading/body detection while `fence=1`. Both the as-is accept test (exit 0)
and the section-removed reject test (exit 1) now behave correctly.

